(More on) What is going on with crime (types) in Phoenix?

02 November, 2020


In a prior post, I talked about what is going on with crime in Phoenix in 2020, noting the considerable decline in crime relative to other years.

Here, I want to further unpack the trends by focusing on crime types.



Monthly Counts over the Years



Let’s pull the most recent data for crime incidents from the site.

The data are reported as UCR crime classifications and have geographic information (block address, zip) as well as the date and time of the incident. As of November, 2020, there were 325,274 crime incidents with complete data from 11/2015 to within a week of the current date.
